com.ibm.ccl.soa.deploy.core
Interface DeployModelObject

All Known Subinterfaces:
AndConstraint, Artifact, AttributeValueConstraint, BooleanOperator, BundleCapability, Capability, CollocationConstraint, CommunicationCapability, CommunicationConstraint, ConceptualNode, ConfigurationContract, Constraint, ConstraintLink, DeferredHostingConstraint, DependencyLink, DeployLink, EnumerationConstraint, ExclusionConstraint, ExplicitContract, FileArtifact, GroupCardinalityConstraint, HostingLink, Import, InstanceConfiguration, Instantiation, MemberCardinalityConstraint, MemberLink, NotConstraint, OrConstraint, RangeConstraint, RealizationLink, Reference, Requirement, RequirementExpression, Service, SoftwareComponent, StructuralConstraint, Topology, TypeConstraint, Unit, UnitLink, VersionConstraint, XorConstraint
public interface DeployModelObject

A representation of the model object 'Deploy Model Object'. Abstract parent type of all deployment types.

The following features are supported:

  • Annotations
  • Attribute Meta Data
  • Extended Attributes
  • Description
  • Display Name
  • Mutable
  • Name

See Also:

addStatus

IStatus addStatus(IStatus aNewStatus)
A modeled object will not overwrite any existing status unless a client calls clearStatus(). Whenever a client calls addStatus(), either the given aNewStatus is set as the status or the given aNewStatus is added to the existing MultiStatus. If there is an existing IStatus an it is not a MultiStatus then a new MultiStatus is created with the existing and the given aNewStatus as child elements. The resultant IStatus is returned.

Parameters:
aNewStatus - A status for this model object (could be warning, error, info, or OK)
Returns:
IStatus - The combined status after adding the given aNewStatus.

clearStatus

void clearStatus()
Reset the status to just IStatus.OK

getFullPath

java.lang.String getFullPath()
Returns the full path of the deploy model object relative to its topology.

Paths are used when serializing link targets and error statuses. Examples include DependencyLink.getTargetURI(), DeployLink.getTargetURI(), ConstraintLink.getTargetURI().

The absolute path is composed listing the getName() of the object's containment path, separated by the '/' character. If a name is not valid or unique in its container, the index escape character '@' is used followed by the containment index. Examples:

  • "/unit1/req1/expr1" : an absolute path rooted in the topology, refers to requirement expression "expr1" contained in requirement "req1" which is contained in the topology-level unit "unit1".
  • "/unit1/@3/expr1": as in the previous example, but using the containment index of the requirement because its name is not unique.
character to the

Equivalent to invoking getRelativePath(DeployModelObject) on getTopology().

Returns:
the path relative to the topology, or null if the object is not directly or indirectly contained in a topology.
See Also:
getRelativePath(DeployModelObject), resolve(String)

isPublic

boolean isPublic()
If the DeployModelObject is from an import, the result reflects the immutable exposure from the Imported Topology's contract. If the DeployModelObject is local (contained by the current Topology, then this method always returns true.

To determine of the DeployModelObject is public in the current Topology's contract, use Topology.getConfigurationContract() and Agreement.isPublic(DeployModelObject).

Returns:
True if the DeployModelObject is public (can be the source of links).

isPublicEditable

boolean isPublicEditable()
If the DeployModelObject is from an import, the result reflects the immutable exposure from the Imported Topology's contract. If the DeployModelObject is local (contained by the current Topology, then this method always returns true.

To determine of the DeployModelObject is public-editable in the current Topology's contract, use Topology.getConfigurationContract() and Agreement.isPublicEditable(DeployModelObject).

Returns:
True if the DeployModelObject is public-editable (can have augmented state associated with it).

isPublicEditable

boolean isPublicEditable(java.lang.String propertyName)
If the DeployModelObject is from an import, the result reflects the immutable exposure from the Imported Topology's contract. If the DeployModelObject is local (contained by the current Topology, then this method always returns true.

To determine of the given property of this DeployModelObject is public-editable in the current Topology's contract, use Topology.getConfigurationContract() and Agreement.isPublicEditable(DeployModelObject, String).

Parameters:
propertyName - The name of a property associated with this DeployModelObject.
Returns:
True if the given property of this DeployModelObject is public-editable (can have augmented state associated with it).
